cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.LG

The paper discusses the security of text-based passwords in the context of usable interfaces, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as participants were asked to generate and recall passwords using different text entry methods. The analysis of structures and probabilities used in the study can be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the vulnerabilities of different text entry methods, which can be considered under social and information networks (cs.SI).
